Is that clear?

01:05:02.762 --> 01:05:04.161
Yes, Mr. Pelaski.

01:05:11.772 --> 01:05:13.452
Could somebody please
tell me where we are?

01:05:14.641 --> 01:05:16.008
We're doing the new ending.

01:05:17.811 --> 01:05:19.779
New ending?

01:05:19.781 --> 01:05:22.449
Yeah, Carl wrote it. They were
working on it when he collapsed.

01:05:23.419 --> 01:05:27.820
Yeah, as long as nobody kills
themselves, it's good with me.

01:05:35.864 --> 01:05:37.464
Fine. Let's just do this.

01:05:39.033 --> 01:05:40.434
Go ahead.

01:05:40.436 --> 01:05:42.336
Do you have any direction?

01:05:45.809 --> 01:05:47.242
You're in pain.

01:05:48.943 --> 01:05:50.811
You're in deep,
unbearable pain.

01:05:53.314 --> 01:05:55.315
"Mother! Oh, my dear mother!"

01:05:55.317 --> 01:05:57.818
"How could you abandon
me to such a cruel fate!"

01:05:57.820 --> 01:06:00.088
Okay, Halle. "A father
who couldn't love me!"

01:06:00.090 --> 01:06:02.323
"A world where I'd never belong!"
That's enough.

01:06:02.325 --> 01:06:04.692
"Oh, God! I want to die..."

01:06:04.694 --> 01:06:07.462
No, my darling!
You must live! Live!

01:06:07.464 --> 01:06:10.065
Knock it off, both of you!

01:06:10.067 --> 01:06:12.334
- Take it seriously.
- Why?

01:06:12.336 --> 01:06:15.237
It sucks. This ending sucks.

01:06:15.239 --> 01:06:18.507
My grandparents are coming in
from Tucson to see me suck.

01:06:19.443 --> 01:06:21.877
This isn't Jason's play anymore.
It's bullshit.

01:06:21.879 --> 01:06:23.079
Hey! Language.

01:06:24.916 --> 01:06:26.249
Where's Jason?

01:06:26.251 --> 01:06:27.851
We want Jason back.

01:06:27.853 --> 01:06:32.222
Okay, that's it. One week
detention, Miss Anderson!

01:06:55.113 --> 01:06:56.914
Yes. I'm coming.

01:07:02.154 --> 01:07:04.889
<i>Jason, please don't make
me stand outside.</i>

01:07:04.891 --> 01:07:08.425
<i>I'm gonna... I'm not going to leave
here until we talk.</i>

01:07:12.966 --> 01:07:14.766
May I come in?

01:07:14.768 --> 01:07:16.001
Yeah.

01:07:23.876 --> 01:07:25.410
May I have a glass of water?

01:07:36.322 --> 01:07:38.558
- I'm here to ask for a favor.
- Are you kidding me?

01:07:38.560 --> 01:07:40.126
If you could just
write a new ending.

01:07:40.128 --> 01:07:42.061
No. No. No.

01:07:42.063 --> 01:07:44.230
- Write a new ending?
- Jason, please...

01:07:44.232 --> 01:07:46.465
For what? To make it happy?
To make it cute and safe?

01:07:46.467 --> 01:07:50.169
I understand that, but I'm in an
untenable situation here...

01:07:50.171 --> 01:07:54.307
slap a feel-good ending
on Death of a Salesman.

01:07:54.309 --> 01:07:55.942
Does he really have to die?

01:07:55.944 --> 01:07:57.310
This isn't helping anyone.

01:07:57.312 --> 01:07:58.478
That's because
nothing's gonna help.

01:07:58.480 --> 01:08:00.081
Everything's fucked,
and it's your fault!

01:08:02.250 --> 01:08:03.817
I want to kill myself.

01:08:03.819 --> 01:08:05.252
That's not an answer, Jason.

01:08:06.988 --> 01:08:08.628
What makes you think
you have the answers?

01:08:10.891 --> 01:08:13.359
I mean, who are you, anyway?

01:08:13.361 --> 01:08:16.264
Who gets a power trip
lecturing teenagers.

01:08:18.434 --> 01:08:22.304
You really think you affect their
lives by reading them Emerson?

01:08:23.973 --> 01:08:25.506
You're a joke.

01:08:25.509 --> 01:08:26.975
They don't respect you.

01:08:28.278 --> 01:08:30.645
The second they finish high school,
they forget you.

01:08:37.120 --> 01:08:38.620
Yes...

01:08:40.457 --> 01:08:42.358
Well...

01:08:44.261 --> 01:08:48.598
I was thinking about your ending,
and I realized that there

01:08:48.600 --> 01:08:53.170
may be something that I missed
in previous readings of your play.

01:08:53.171 --> 01:08:54.970
And that is...

01:08:54.973 --> 01:08:57.273
That the ending sucks.

01:08:57.274 --> 01:08:59.140
What?

01:08:59.143 --> 01:09:03.279
Everyone kills themselves?
That's your resolution?

01:09:03.281 --> 01:09:06.249
Jason, come on.
What do you think?

01:09:08.051 --> 01:09:09.553
You said, you loved the ending.

01:09:09.555 --> 01:09:14.024
Well, you know, I do make mistakes,
as you know.

01:09:15.193 --> 01:09:17.194
Whatever. I'm done with this.

01:09:17.196 --> 01:09:19.563
You know, sometimes
you can't run away.

01:09:19.564 --> 01:09:21.430
And you can't go to law school.

01:09:21.433 --> 01:09:24.167
And you can't kill yourself.

01:09:24.169 --> 01:09:27.604
Because sometimes you have to stay
and suck it up.

01:09:27.606 --> 01:09:29.573
- Fuck you!
- Can you just try?

01:09:29.576 --> 01:09:33.578
I mean, can you imagine that
there might be another ending?

01:09:33.580 --> 01:09:37.314
A different ending,
where everyone doesn't die.

01:09:39.952 --> 01:09:42.286
No! Get the fuck
out of my house!

01:10:03.000 --> 01:10:10.000
Hmun dang zawng aia tlawma
Air Tickets la duh tan.

01:10:20.002 --> 01:10:27.002
In/Office lamah pawh a thlawnin
tickets kan dahsak thei.

01:11:12.549 --> 01:11:15.083
This is horrible.
They're gonna hate it.

01:11:15.085 --> 01:11:18.286
Halle... I can't, I can't,
I can't do this!

01:11:18.288 --> 01:11:21.357
No, no. I can't... I can't remember
any of my lines.

01:11:21.359 --> 01:11:25.395
Just say them the way we rehearsed
them last week and you'll be terrific.

01:11:25.397 --> 01:11:27.430
I know. I heard you.

01:11:27.432 --> 01:11:29.232
- All right?
- Thank you.

01:11:29.234 --> 01:11:30.700
- Yeah.
- All right.

01:11:30.702 --> 01:11:32.536
All right. Five minutes.

01:11:32.538 --> 01:11:34.772
It's five minutes, everyone.

01:11:34.774 --> 01:11:36.506
All right, you've
worked really hard.

01:11:36.508 --> 01:11:38.141
And you know what to do.

01:11:38.143 --> 01:11:39.709
And you're going to be great.

01:11:39.711 --> 01:11:42.645
And you should all feel
so proud of yourselves.

01:11:42.647 --> 01:11:46.450
- Hello, my children of the night.
- Mr. Kapinas!

01:11:46.452 --> 01:11:47.684
I'm back.

01:11:47.686 --> 01:11:49.453
Mr. Kapinas, you made it.

01:11:49.455 --> 01:11:52.222
Wild horses couldn't
keep me away.

01:11:52.224 --> 01:11:54.424
Dear, dear Linda.

01:11:54.426 --> 01:11:57.095
I am eternally grateful
for all your help,

01:11:57.097 --> 01:11:59.164
and understanding.

01:11:59.166 --> 01:12:01.598
It was no problem. How are you?

01:12:01.600 --> 01:12:04.101
Much better, thank you.
Fully rested,

01:12:04.103 --> 01:12:07.204
mildly medicated and ready
to resume my duties.

01:12:07.206 --> 01:12:09.374
Well, I think,
everything's under control.

01:12:09.376 --> 01:12:13.611
Don't worry,
I've done this a thousand times.

01:12:13.613 --> 01:12:15.747
Why don't you relax?
Take a seat, enjoy the show.

01:12:15.749 --> 01:12:18.116
Thespians. It's time.

01:12:18.118 --> 01:12:19.517
Prayer circle of love
and commitment?

01:12:19.519 --> 01:12:21.453
Prayer circle of love
and commitment.

01:12:23.622 --> 01:12:26.325
My future Tony Award winners,

01:12:26.327 --> 01:12:27.493
let's all take a deep breath.

01:12:29.863 --> 01:12:31.864
Let it go.

01:12:31.866 --> 01:12:33.432
Focus.

01:12:33.434 --> 01:12:35.268
And as Meryl Streep once said,

01:12:35.270 --> 01:12:38.205
when we were doing
Shakespeare in the Park,

01:12:38.207 --> 01:12:40.106
"Speak up!"

01:12:55.156 --> 01:12:56.790
Here we are.

01:12:59.661 --> 01:13:01.929
Next year, we are definitely
doing Our Town.

01:13:27.724 --> 01:13:29.826
Why are you not
at the hospital?

01:13:46.843 --> 01:13:48.878
- Are you going in?
- I'm too nervous.

01:13:54.486 --> 01:13:59.554
<i>They were pink roses. That must be
a good sign, I'm sure of it!</i>

01:13:59.556 --> 01:14:03.605
<i>No, Jane. She's gone.
She died this morning.</i>

01:14:03.640 --> 01:14:05.895
I don't understand, you said she was
getting better. You...

01:14:05.897 --> 01:14:08.197
She took a turn.

01:14:08.199 --> 01:14:10.466
<i>No. No.</i>

01:14:10.468 --> 01:14:13.203
<i>I'm sorry.
It happened so suddenly.</i>

01:14:13.205 --> 01:14:14.872
<i>She never woke up again.</i>

01:14:14.874 --> 01:14:16.907
<i>Then, she was gone.</i>

01:14:16.909 --> 01:14:18.375
<i>But I never got to say goodbye.</i>

01:14:18.377 --> 01:14:20.476
<i>You told me that, I would see her
one last time.</i>

01:14:20.478 --> 01:14:21.644
Why didn't you come get me?

01:14:21.646 --> 01:14:23.613
It would not have
changed anything.

01:14:23.615 --> 01:14:25.749
<i>I could have been there to tell her
that I love her.</i>

01:14:25.751 --> 01:14:27.885
<i>I could have held her hand so she
wouldn't have felt so alone.</i>

01:14:27.887 --> 01:14:29.887
<i>Jane, control yourself.</i>

01:14:29.889 --> 01:14:31.990
<i>I must prepare for the funeral.</i>

01:14:31.992 --> 01:14:33.625
<i>It's time to move on.</i>

01:14:38.398 --> 01:14:39.865
<i>I never knew my mother.</i>

01:14:39.867 --> 01:14:41.967
<i>But she was beautiful...</i>

01:14:43.002 --> 01:14:45.704
<i>She loved bright
and colorful things.</i>

01:14:45.706 --> 01:14:48.340
<i>Here. I'll give you
your favorite colors.</i>

01:14:48.342 --> 01:14:50.609
<i>Green for her wings.</i>

01:14:50.611 --> 01:14:53.512
<i>Green with flecks of gold,
just like her eyes.</i>

01:14:59.252 --> 01:15:00.786
Pleasure to meet you.
I'm Margaret.

01:15:03.458 --> 01:15:06.959
Did you hear me?
I said step away!

01:15:07.961 --> 01:15:09.328
Damn it, Jane!

01:15:12.666 --> 01:15:13.866
That's not me.

01:15:33.822 --> 01:15:36.724
Mother. I'm ready.

01:15:36.726 --> 01:15:39.294
Yes, daughter.
Come away with me.

01:15:39.296 --> 01:15:41.663
You'll never belong
in this world.

01:15:41.665 --> 01:15:46.402
<i>All the pain and the fear
and the loneliness.</i>

01:15:46.404 --> 01:15:48.536
We'll be together, always.

01:15:50.305 --> 01:15:51.739
Jane! Get away.

01:15:51.741 --> 01:15:53.641
<i>- Please listen to me.
- Get out!</i>

01:15:53.643 --> 01:15:55.710
<i>You ruined everything.
My entire life.</i>

01:15:55.712 --> 01:15:58.446
<i>I know, I've made mistakes.
I'm sorry.</i>

01:15:58.448 --> 01:16:01.983
<i>I wish I could go back and change
what happened, but I can't.</i>

01:16:01.985 --> 01:16:04.853
<i>Please, Jane,
I'm asking for another chance.</i>

01:16:04.855 --> 01:16:07.923
<i>It's not too late...
I know you want to run away,</i>

01:16:07.925 --> 01:16:09.992
<i>I know you want to punish me,</i>

01:16:09.994 --> 01:16:11.960
<i>maybe I deserve it...</i>

01:16:13.496 --> 01:16:15.997
It's better than I thought...

01:16:15.999 --> 01:16:18.467
<i>You do deserve it!
You're the monster. Not me!</i>

01:16:18.469 --> 01:16:21.003
<i>I know... I know, I am.
I'm so sorry...</i>

01:16:21.005 --> 01:16:22.704
What the fuck is this?

01:16:22.706 --> 01:16:24.206
Jason.

01:16:31.415 --> 01:16:33.083
At least in New York they didn't
give a shit about my play,

01:16:33.085 --> 01:16:34.517
they didn't try to destroy it.

01:16:34.519 --> 01:16:36.020
It's not destroyed.
It's still your play.

01:16:36.022 --> 01:16:37.821
You've ruined the
whole point of the story.

01:16:37.823 --> 01:16:41.125
Jason, I was wrong. I didn't know
what to do, or how to fix it.

01:16:41.127 --> 01:16:43.360
And I'm sorry.

01:16:43.362 --> 01:16:46.363
I am truly, truly sorry.

01:16:46.365 --> 01:16:50.267
Please don't let my mistakes stand
in the way of your success.

01:17:41.890 --> 01:17:43.658
Thank you.

01:17:47.095 --> 01:17:48.762
You were wonderful.

01:18:19.093 --> 01:18:20.862
Author! Author!

01:18:24.500 --> 01:18:25.867
He means you.

01:18:29.872 --> 01:18:31.372
Go on.

01:18:35.244 --> 01:18:36.711
There he is.

01:19:34.307 --> 01:19:36.008
Ms. Sinclair.

01:19:37.277 --> 01:19:39.144
Nice work.

01:19:39.146 --> 01:19:40.312
Thank you.

01:19:41.214 --> 01:19:43.247
May I apologize
for my behavior?

01:19:43.249 --> 01:19:45.851
Oh, no. Forget about it, it wasn't my
finest moment either.

01:19:45.853 --> 01:19:49.555
I shouldn't have believed that stuff
from the play. I was ridiculous.

01:19:49.557 --> 01:19:50.790
I'm very sorry.

01:19:52.293 --> 01:19:54.227
Apology accepted.

01:19:54.229 --> 01:19:55.695
Thank you.

01:19:55.697 --> 01:19:57.697
It's actually true.

01:19:58.832 --> 01:20:01.001
Sort of.

01:20:01.003 --> 01:20:03.237
About the play.

01:20:03.239 --> 01:20:05.039
I wasn't a great dad.

01:20:06.708 --> 01:20:10.742
Pushed him to do all the things
I wanted him to do.

01:20:10.744 --> 01:20:12.378
I'm sure, you did your best.

01:20:13.314 --> 01:20:16.115
I dated some crazy women.
None of them Irish.

01:20:16.117 --> 01:20:18.084
But...

01:20:18.086 --> 01:20:20.253
Creative license, I guess.

01:20:20.255 --> 01:20:22.922
Anyway, we learn from
our mistakes, right?

01:20:22.924 --> 01:20:24.725
Yes, we do.

01:20:26.261 --> 01:20:28.429
- Good luck with everything.
- Thank you.

01:20:34.835 --> 01:20:39.773
<i>And so, Linda Sinclair resumed
her life as a schoolteacher.</i>

01:20:39.775 --> 01:20:42.910
<i>Though she brought a new,
modern approach to her craft.</i>

01:20:42.912 --> 01:20:45.312
Now that you've
all finished the reading,

01:20:45.314 --> 01:20:48.751
let's try a little
creative writing exercise.

01:20:48.753 --> 01:20:52.787
I'd like you all to write a new
ending to A Tale of Two Cities.

01:20:52.789 --> 01:20:55.156
Now, it could be
anything you like.

01:20:55.158 --> 01:20:58.293
So let your
imaginations run wild.

01:20:58.295 --> 01:21:00.295
<i>She often saw Dr. Sherwood,</i>

01:21:00.297 --> 01:21:04.633
<i>though propriety dictated that
she maintain a respectable distance</i>

01:21:04.635 --> 01:21:09.038
<i>from the father of the young man
with whom she'd so disgraced herself.</i>

01:21:13.678 --> 01:21:16.011
That's a good biography.

01:21:16.013 --> 01:21:17.913
I have a copy if you
want to borrow it.

01:21:18.982 --> 01:21:21.984
- You're a fan?
- Of Conan Doyle?

01:21:21.986 --> 01:21:23.853
- Of course.
- Me too.

01:21:23.855 --> 01:21:25.689
Since I was a kid.

01:21:25.691 --> 01:21:28.759
<i>And that was the end of it.</i>

01:21:28.761 --> 01:21:30.761
How are you?

01:21:30.763 --> 01:21:32.396
I'm pretty good, thanks.

01:21:34.832 --> 01:21:37.300
Hey, would you like to grab
a cup of coffee or something?

01:21:37.302 --> 01:21:38.669
<i>Naturally...</i>

01:21:39.705 --> 01:21:41.204
<i>She refused.</i>

01:21:42.140 --> 01:21:44.040
Okay. Why not.

01:21:44.042 --> 01:21:47.878
<i>And so they spoke in
a strictly impersonal way.</i>

01:21:47.880 --> 01:21:49.414
She did some crazy stuff.

01:21:49.416 --> 01:21:52.818
She had a yard sale one time when
I was out of town,

01:21:52.820 --> 01:21:55.320
and sold my entire collection of
Ellery Queen first editions.

01:21:55.322 --> 01:21:57.222
- Oh, no!
- Yes!

01:21:58.358 --> 01:22:02.026
That's when I knew the marriage
was kinda over.

01:22:02.028 --> 01:22:04.329
<i>They did not discuss the boy.</i>

01:22:04.331 --> 01:22:06.098
- Jason's doing really well.
- Is he?

01:22:06.100 --> 01:22:08.467
Yeah, yeah, he's actually written
another piece.

01:22:08.469 --> 01:22:12.304
And he's work shopping it in a
children's theater in New Jersey.

01:22:12.306 --> 01:22:15.208
I mean, you may or may not realize
some references to Orwell,

01:22:15.210 --> 01:22:16.709
and Kafka in the first act...

01:22:16.711 --> 01:22:18.377
Oh, that's so wonderful.

01:22:18.379 --> 01:22:20.145
Can I be honest
with you about something?

01:22:20.147 --> 01:22:21.914
<i>I knew it.</i>

01:22:21.916 --> 01:22:29.021
The whole time we're strolling along here,
I keep thinking...

01:22:29.023 --> 01:22:32.758
You know,
you slept with my son.

01:22:32.760 --> 01:22:38.263
I understand that it was just one
of those things or whatever, but...

01:22:39.967 --> 01:22:42.402
I guess, what I am
trying to say is...

01:22:45.039 --> 01:22:46.873
I still think
you're pretty great.

01:22:46.875 --> 01:22:48.740
What?

01:22:48.742 --> 01:22:50.275
Yeah.

01:22:50.277 --> 01:22:54.014
And if it's not too weird...

01:22:54.016 --> 01:22:56.150
For you, or me...

01:22:56.152 --> 01:23:00.955
Walter Mosley's speaking over at
Wilkes next week, and I thought maybe...

01:23:00.957 --> 01:23:04.325
<i>Linda Sinclair.
What are you doing?</i>

01:23:04.327 --> 01:23:07.796
<i>You belong here.
At home. Alone.</i>

01:23:07.798 --> 01:23:09.431
<i>You don't want to go out there.</i>

01:23:09.433 --> 01:23:12.433
<i>It's a cruel and
unforgiving world.</i>

01:23:12.435 --> 01:23:13.534
<i>Linda.</i>

01:23:13.536 --> 01:23:15.302
- Hi, Linda.
- Hi.

01:23:15.304 --> 01:23:16.403
Linda.

01:23:16.405 --> 01:23:17.939
You look great.

01:23:17.941 --> 01:23:19.374
Thank you.

01:23:19.376 --> 01:23:21.443
Are you ready?

01:23:21.445 --> 01:23:23.078
Yes, I am.

01:23:23.080 --> 01:23:26.980
<i>Linda? Are you listening to me?
Don't be a fool!</i>

